Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, March 12 (XINHUA) -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin ordered the Defense Ministry today to formulate measures 
for retargeting Russian strategic nuclear missiles away from the 
United States and Britain. 
  The order was given to implement the Moscow agreement signed 
by the Russian and U.S. presidents on January 14, and to 
implement the joint statement issued by Yeltsin and British 
Prime Minister John Major on February 15, the Presidential Press 
Office said. 
  According to the two agreements, the two sides will retarget 
their nuclear missiles away from each other by May 30. 

